# lesson 8 list style

---



### order list

```css
ol {
  list-style-type: lower-alpha;
  padding: 2px;
}
```

set the symbol in front of the list



#### example

circle, decimal-leading-zero, lower alpha, upper-roman



### unorder list

```css
ul {
  list-style-type: square;
  color: blue; change all the text and disc
  line-height: 1.6;
  list-style-image: url('../images/checkmark.png');use image as bullet point
}
```



### some more

```css
ul li:nth-child(odd) {
  color: red;
}
```

only the odd of the li turn red

#### put marker into alignment

```css
ul {
  list-style-position: inside; vary for different browser
}
```



### marker

```css
::marker {
  color: red;
  font-family: fantasy;
  font-size: 1.5em;
  content:"Only $5 >>"
}
```

directly edit the colon or marker

